    {
      "id": "tx2",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 41.76204321959415,
      "y": 182.18353905748762,
      "width": 770.0408935546875,
      "height": 227.5,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#000000",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1,
      "version": 687,
      "versionNonce": 123259207,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "text": "2) Non-Functional Requirements( The system must...? )\nAvail / DR: Separate control-plane vs data-plane SLOs (DP counts admitted traffic only); \n    RPO/RTO defined per failure class (component, dependency, zonal, regional); \n    explicit region-failure and degraded-mode behavior; serving traffic is prioritized over making changes during incidents.\nScale / Geo: Scale defined by tenants × users × ops/sec × read/write mix × data growth; \n    multi-region mode (active/active or active/passive); \n    sharding and data-locality rules; global vs regional access semantics.\nLatency: Admitted-traffic p50/p95/p99 latency with payload bounds; \n    cold-start latency explicitly bounded and limited to deploy, scale, or failover events.\nOperability: Golden signals (latency, traffic, errors, saturation) per tenant and globally; SLO burn-rate paging; \n    capacity or budget trends create tickets; rollback supports auto/manual triggers with bounded blast radius \n        and defined time-to-recover.\nSecurity / Cost: Strong authentication and authorization; immutable audit logs; enforced quotas and budgets; \n    data retention and PII handling policies.",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "2) Non-Functional Requirements( The system must...? )\nAvail / DR: Separate control-plane vs data-plane SLOs (DP counts admitted traffic only); \n    RPO/RTO defined per failure class (component, dependency, zonal, regional); \n    explicit region-failure and degraded-mode behavior; serving traffic is prioritized over making changes during incidents.\nScale / Geo: Scale defined by tenants × users × ops/sec × read/write mix × data growth; \n    multi-region mode (active/active or active/passive); \n    sharding and data-locality rules; global vs regional access semantics.\nLatency: Admitted-traffic p50/p95/p99 latency with payload bounds; \n    cold-start latency explicitly bounded and limited to deploy, scale, or failover events.\nOperability: Golden signals (latency, traffic, errors, saturation) per tenant and globally; SLO burn-rate paging; \n    capacity or budget trends create tickets; rollback supports auto/manual triggers with bounded blast radius \n        and defined time-to-recover.\nSecurity / Cost: Strong authentication and authorization; immutable audit logs; enforced quotas and budgets; \n    data retention and PII handling policies.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
