    },
    {
      "id": "st2",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 35.94376438811082,
      "y": 435.69914763078026,
      "width": 924.2107424318606,
      "height": 390,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#000000",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1,
      "version": 633,
      "versionNonce": 1247539623,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "text": "Named Invariants (apply to all flows)\n\nEach: Name (2–4 words), Rule (must always / never; if…then…), Prevents (1 line)\n\nPrompt to generate invariants: “What must never happen—even during failure, retries, or scale?”\n\nCommon classes (with examples):\n Promotion safety: \n        Example: Explicit Promotion Gate — No model/config may serve production traffic unless explicitly approved.\n        Prevents: unreviewed or partial releases.\n Tenant isolation\n        Example: Strict Tenant Isolation — Inference execution and resource usage must never cross tenant boundaries.\n        Prevents: noisy neighbors and data leakage.\n Budget semantics\n        Example: Fail-Closed Budget Enforcement — If a tenant exceeds budget, requests are rejected or degraded, never oversubscribed.\n        Prevents: runaway cost and fairness violations.\n Audit immutability\n        Example: Immutable Change History — All config and approval events are append-only and replayable.\n        Prevents: silent state changes and irreproducible rollbacks.\n Degraded-mode contract\n        Example: Control Plane Independence — If the control plane is unavailable, the data plane continues serving admitted traffic.\n        Prevents: full outages due to admin workflows.\n\n(Pick 2–3 that actually constrain the design.)",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Named Invariants (apply to all flows)\n\nEach: Name (2–4 words), Rule (must always / never; if…then…), Prevents (1 line)\n\nPrompt to generate invariants: “What must never happen—even during failure, retries, or scale?”\n\nCommon classes (with examples):\n Promotion safety: \n        Example: Explicit Promotion Gate — No model/config may serve production traffic unless explicitly approved.\n        Prevents: unreviewed or partial releases.\n Tenant isolation\n        Example: Strict Tenant Isolation — Inference execution and resource usage must never cross tenant boundaries.\n        Prevents: noisy neighbors and data leakage.\n Budget semantics\n        Example: Fail-Closed Budget Enforcement — If a tenant exceeds budget, requests are rejected or degraded, never oversubscribed.\n        Prevents: runaway cost and fairness violations.\n Audit immutability\n        Example: Immutable Change History — All config and approval events are append-only and replayable.\n        Prevents: silent state changes and irreproducible rollbacks.\n Degraded-mode contract\n        Example: Control Plane Independence — If the control plane is unavailable, the data plane continues serving admitted traffic.\n        Prevents: full outages due to admin workflows.\n\n(Pick 2–3 that actually constrain the design.)",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "index": "aE",
      "frameId": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768513835497,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "autoResize": false
